message:
{{#is_alert}}
🔴 *query0 HotShot view-timeout rate is ABOVE its normal baseline.*
The number of `view timed out` events on the testnet/main **query0** node in the last hour is anomalously high vs its trailing baseline (~24h, daily seasonality).

A single timeout = one view that missed its deadline. Escalation to watch for (`crates/hotshot/task-impls/src/view_sync.rs`):
• `Starting view sync protocol` (error) → ≥2 consecutive timeouts, recovery engaged
• `Too many consecutive timeouts! This shouldn't happen` (error) → ≥3 consecutive, liveness at risk

Logs: https://app.datadoghq.com/logs?query=%40aws.awslogs.logGroup%3A%22%2Ftestnet%2Fmain%2F%22%20%40aws.awslogs.logStream%3A%2A0%2Fquery%2A%20%22view%20timed%20out%22
{{/is_alert}}
{{#is_recovery}}
✅ query0 view-timeout rate is back within the normal baseline.
{{/is_recovery}}

